## Research Findings: Calendar Features

### Google Calendar Features (2025)

**Core Scheduling:**
- Multiple calendar views (day/week/month/year/agenda)
- Recurring events (daily/weekly/monthly/yearly with custom rules)
- All-day events
- Multi-day events
- Time zone support (multiple time zones, travel mode)
- Event reminders (5min/15min/30min/1hr/1day/custom)
- Event notifications (email/push/in-app)

**Advanced Features:**
- **Appointment Scheduling:** Create booking pages with availability
- **Focus Time:** Block time for deep work (auto-decline meetings)
- **Office Hours:** Auto-decline meetings outside work hours
- **Out of Office:** Auto-decline + notify during absence
- **Working Hours:** Set default work schedule
- **Working Location:** Track office/home/remote
- **Tasks Integration:** Link Google Tasks to calendar dates
- **Goals:** Schedule time for personal goals
- **Event Color Coding:** Visual organization
- **Calendar Sharing:** Multiple permission levels (see all/see free-busy/make changes)
- **Find a Time:** See attendee availability
- **Speedy Meetings:** Auto-shorten meetings (25min instead of 30min)
- **World Clock:** Multiple time zones in sidebar
- **Advanced Search:** Filter by attendees/location/date range
- **Event Attachments:** Add files/links to events
- **Video Conferencing:** Built-in Google Meet integration

**Integrations:**
- Gmail (auto-create events from emails)
- Google Meet (one-click video calls)
- Google Tasks (task management)
- Google Drive (document sharing)
- Third-party integrations (Zoom, Slack, etc.)

### Notion Calendar Features (formerly Cron)

**Notion Integration:**
- Connect Notion docs/projects/timelines to events
- View Notion database items as calendar events (deadlines, milestones)
- Edit database items from calendar (two-way sync)
- Quick access to meeting notes in Notion

**Modern UX:**
- Beautiful light/dark modes
- Keyboard shortcuts (Cmd+K command palette, "S" to share availability)
- Menu bar widget (macOS) - see schedule and join meetings from menu bar
- Widgets (multiple sizes, rich previews, quick-add button)
- Multiple time zones (drag to "travel to any city")

**Scheduling:**
- Built-in availability sharing (no external tools needed)
- Auto-blocking to prevent double-booking
- Deep Google Calendar sync
- Zoom and Google Meet integration

**Platform:**
- Cross-platform (macOS, Windows, iOS, Android, web)
- 12 languages support
- **Free** (competitive advantage)

### Linear Calendar Integration (via Reclaim.ai & Morgen)

**Task-Calendar Sync:**
- Auto-schedule Linear issues in calendar
- Time blocking for task work
- Priority-based scheduling
- Auto-reschedule when priorities shift
- Plan week with task scheduling
- Drag tasks to different time blocks

### Motion (AI Scheduling)

**AI Features:**
- Enter task with time estimate, priority, start/due date
- AI organizes day and schedules tasks automatically
- Auto-shift tasks when urgent items arise
- Intelligent time blocking

